123
13:55.920 --> 14:03.560
We're only using single cubic gates here, so it's kind of trivial in a way, but in any case, gadgets such as this won't cause errors to

124
14:03.560 --> 14:09.600
propagate. Now, any one of the individual gates in a gadget such as this could fail, and that will introduce

125
14:09.600 --> 14:16.240
errors, but will always perform error correction immediately after every gadget. And as long as the error rate is

126
14:16.240 --> 14:21.040
low enough, the error correcting code will correct those errors.

127
14:21.040 --> 14:25.680
And like I said, this is always possible for polygates for every stabilizer code.

