14:33.880 --> 14:40.320
for. For another example which does involve two cubic gates. This time we can consider transversal implementations

130
14:40.320 --> 14:47.279
of C not gates. In particular, for every CSS code, we can always implement a C not gate

131
14:47.279 --> 14:53.560
between two logical cubits by simply performing C not gates on corresponding pairs of physical

132
14:53.560 --> 15:00.000
cubits. And this satisfies the condition of being transversal because each of these individual C not gates acts only

133
15:00.000 --> 15:07.680
on a single cubit position within each code block. For example, the first C not gate acts only on the topmost cubit

134
15:07.680 --> 15:13.959
within each code block. the second C not gates acts only on the second from top cubit and so

135
15:13.959 --> 15:20.000
on. In this case, we could have a propagation of errors because C not gates propagate errors and there's no

136
15:20.000 --> 15:27.279
way to prevent that. But the key is that the error propagation never happens within a single code block. For example,

137
15:27.279 --> 15:34.240
an X error could occur on the top cubit of the top code block right before the gadget is performed and the first C not

138
15:34.240 --> 15:40.639
within the gadget will propagate that error to the top cubit in the lower block. But the two resulting errors are

139
15:40.639 --> 15:48.800
now in separate code blocks. So the error correction steps that take place after the gadget will be able to correct those errors individually because those

140
15:48.800 --> 15:53.279
errors only affect a single cubit within each code block.

141
15:53.279 --> 15:59.759
In contrast, if the error propagation happened inside of the same code block, then we might be in trouble because the

142
15:59.759 --> 16:05.839
error propagation is then turning a lowway error into a higher way error that our code may not be able to handle.

143
16:05.839 --> 16:12.320
This implementation doesn't work for nonCSS codes, but as long as we use a CSS code, we can always implement C not

144
16:12.320 --> 16:18.399
gates transversely in this way. And for one more example, every

145
16:18.399 --> 16:26.120
Clifford gate can be implemented transversely for the steam code. And in fact for any color code which is one of the really nice things about color

146
16:26.120 --> 16:33.519
