147
16:33.519 --> 16:40.720
each of the physical cubits and a logical sgate can be implemented not by an sgate on each cubit but rather by an

148
16:40.720 --> 16:48.480
s dagger gate on each physical cubit. So the upshot is that transversal gate implementations are inherently

149
16:48.480 --> 16:55.839
fault tolerant because they never propagate errors within a single code block which gives the error correction steps a fighting chance to correct

150
16:55.839 --> 17:03.279
whatever errors are introduced or propagated by the gates used for these gadgets. So that's great and it's a

151
17:03.279 --> 17:10.480
really simple way to build fault tolerant gadgets and there are different codes that allow for transversal implementations of different gates such

152
17:10.480 --> 17:17.360
as T gates but unfortunately it's impossible for any non-trivial code to implement a

153
17:17.360 --> 17:25.039
universal set of gates transversely which is a fact known as the eastern canel theorem in more technical terms what it

