156
17:39.520 --> 17:46.720
sets necessarily generate infinitely many operations. I won't explain the proof of this theorem which makes use of some

157
17:46.720 --> 17:52.960
basic facts about lee groupoups and lee algebbras which are not prerequisites for this series. But the basic idea is

158
17:52.960 --> 17:59.600
that infinite families of transversal operations can't possibly keep us inside of the code space because minuscule

159
17:59.600 --> 18:07.240
differences in transversal operations are well approximated by lowweight poly operations which the code detects as

160
18:07.240 --> 18:14.240
errors. So we're very happy when we can implement gates transversely. But for whatever code we choose, we know that we

